body:
I thought it was meant to punish people who intentionally leave games or idle during matches?

Why am I punished so harshly over a couple crashes, dc's or bugsplats/firewall errors that are out of my control wtf?

I'm already on the 20min low priority queue over a couple cases of dc'ing NOT afking. Never have I purposely left a game so I don't understand why I face the risk of a permanent ban after putting 4 years into this game with so much RP spent why should it be thrown away in under a month all because of this new LeaverBuster system which isn't actually fulfilling its intended purpose. Note; In every one of my dc games that have contributed to my penalties...I rejoin as quick as I can and catch up to win. If my teammates have no problem with it (actually they are usually very understanding/nice) then what's the big idea!? {{item:3151}}
